    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>finely</p><p>Cut your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel the skin off your <strong>smoked mackerel fillet[s] </strong>and discard</p><p>Tear the <strong>smoked mackerel</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tortiglioni is almost done, reboil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under the <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out as possible and chop roughly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped spinach </strong>and<strong> smoked mackerel pieces </strong>to the pan with the <strong>drained tortiglioni</strong> and a big splash of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong>,<strong> </strong>then cook for 1-2 min until the fish is warmed through</p><p>Add your<strong> cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche </strong>and<strong> </strong>the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>to the pan with your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully combined and the sauce begins to stick to the tortiglioni \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy smoked mackerel tortiglioni with chilli & lemon</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-smoked-mackerel-tortiglioni-with-chilli-and-lemon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy smoked mackerel tortiglioni with chilli & lemon</strong></p><p>Top with a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Serve with a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
